Shaikh '''Abdullah Mohammed Al-Hugail''' (born 1942, [[Al Majma'ah]], [[Saudi Arabia]]) is a Businessman. He is the former and longest-serving Chairman of the Saudi British Bank [[The Saudi British Bank|SABB]] (an affiliate of the [[HSBC Group]]) for nearly twenty two years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arab Funds Pledge to Raise Over $1bn for Tsunami Relief |url=http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=57496&d=14&m=1&y=2005 |work=[[Arab News]] |date=14 January 2005 |accessdate=18 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616060606/http://archive.arabnews.com/?page=1&section=0&article=57496&d=14&m=1&y=2005 |archivedate=16 June 2012 }}</ref> From 1997 to 2005 he was a member of the [[Majlis]] [[Consultative Assembly of Saudi Arabia|Al Shura]]. He received his Degree in [[Arabic Language]] and [[Arabic literature|Literature]], from [[Imam Muhammad bin Saud Islamic University]] in [[Riyadh]].
==Past occupations== *1962 - 1963 Assistant Secretary General for Administrative Affairs, Higher Planning Council (Saudi Arabia) *1963 - 1964 Director General of Financial Administrative Affairs, Central Planning Committee (Saudi Arabia) *1964 - 1969 Director General of Staff Affairs, Department of Municipal Affairs in the Ministry of Internal Affairs (Saudi Arabia) *1969 - 1974 Assistant Deputy Minister, Ministry of Municipal and Rural Affairs (Saudi Arabia) *1974 - 1975 Deputy Minister, Ministry of Municipal and Rural Affairs (Saudi Arabia) *1975 - 2009 Chairman and President of the Trading & Development Partnership (Saudi Arabia) *1987 - 2009 Chairman of the Saudi British Bank (SABB) an affiliate of HSBC Holdings Plc *1988 - 1996 Member of Al Riyadh Provincial Council Chaired by Prince Salman Bin Abdulaziz, Governor of Riyadh Province *1997 - 2005 Member of Majlis Al Shura (Saudi Arabia) <!-- Image with unknown copyright status removed: [[Image:abdullah.jpg]] -->
